    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Paper Wasp Thr6-bradykinin Oligopeptide-1 Amide is a single chain protein synthetically produced in which a portion of the peptide is identical to the protein, s-Paper Wasp Thr6-bradykinin. The peptide contains 23 amino acids consisting of alanine, arginine, aspartic acid, glycine, isoleucine, leucine, lysine, phenylalanine, proline, threonine and tryptophan in which the C-terminus is an amide. Thr6-Bradykinin contains 9 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
